{
    "Description": "<h3>Usage</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">component.fields()\n</pre><ul><li>Returns a Lua table containing the <strong>current (decrypted) values</strong> of all custom fields for the component.</li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Notes</h3><ul><li>Custom fields are key-value pairs that allow you to parameterize a component’s behavior without modifying its code. They’re especially useful for reusable components that need to be configured differently across instances.</li><li>Each field’s definition (its name, type, and default value) is stored in the <code>config.json</code> file within the component’s Translator project.</li><li>The actual values for these fields are entered via the component’s configuration card in the UI. These values are stored separately from the codebase in the <code>component.json</code> file and are encrypted at rest for security.</li><li>When accessed using <code>component.fields()</code>, the returned Lua table contains the decrypted field values in plain text.</li><li>Permissions may vary where some users may be allowed to edit custom field values but not the component’s code.</li><li>Custom fields can also be used to store state values that survive restarts.</li><li><strong>Security Reminder:</strong> Since <code>component.fields()</code> returns decrypted data at runtime, handle sensitive fields (e.g., API keys, credentials) with care to avoid unintentional logging or exposure.</li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Returns</h3><ul><li>A Lua table (<em>table</em>) where:</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><strong>Keys</strong> are the names of the custom fields,</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><strong>Values</strong> are their corresponding current (decrypted) values.</li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Example</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">-- Get the custom fields of the component\nlocal fields = component.fields()\n\n-- Access a specific field by name\nlocal apiKey = fields[\"API_KEY\"]\n\ntrace(apiKey)\n-- Output: \"&lt;your decrypted key here&gt;\"&nbsp; (decrypted at runtime)\n</pre>",
    "Name": "component.fields",
    "Parameters": null,
    "ParameterTable": false,
    "SummaryLine": "Returns the component’s custom fields as a Lua table."
}